<article id="post-24408" class="post-24408 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-open-mike tag-biomedical-workforce tag-diversity Issue-late-may-early-june-2023">
	<div class="entry-list-content">
		    
    <div class="list-block">
      <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2023/05/18/learn-more-about-unites-progress-towards-ensuring-equity-and-opportunity-in-biomedical-research/" rel="bookmark">Learn More About UNITE’s Progress Towards Ensuring Equity and Opportunity in Biomedical Research</a></h2>      <div class="date-field">May 18, 2023</div>
      <div class="author-field">
        <span><div class="author-meta">By <span><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/lauerm/" title="Posts by Mike Lauer" class="author url fn" rel="author">Mike Lauer</a></span></div></span>
      </div>
      <div><p>The UNITE E Committee recently updated the research community on their progress towards creating a “multipronged strategy to advance racial equity and create the most inclusive biomedical research environment possible.” We wanted to briefly share a few of their efforts here.</p>
</div>
      <div class="tags-field"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/biomedical-workforce/" rel="tag">Biomedical Workforce</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/diversity/" rel="tag">Diversity</a></div>
      <div class="comments-bubble">
        <p><span class="bubble number">0</span> <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2023/05/18/learn-more-about-unites-progress-towards-ensuring-equity-and-opportunity-in-biomedical-research/#comments">Comments</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- .entry-list-content -->

</article><!-- #post-24408 -->

<article id="post-24175" class="post-24175 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-open-mike tag-diversity tag-diversity-equity-inclusion-and-accessibility tag-scientific-workforce-diversity tag-strategic-plan Issue-late-march-2023">
	<div class="entry-list-content">
		    
    <div class="list-block">
      <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2023/03/20/learn-about-nihs-diversity-equity-inclusion-and-accessibility-strategic-plan-for-fy-2023-to-2027/" rel="bookmark">Learn About NIH’s Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Accessibility Strategic Plan for FY 2023 to 2027</a></h2>      <div class="date-field">March 20, 2023</div>
      <div class="author-field">
        <span><div class="author-meta">By <span><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/lauerm/" title="Posts by Mike Lauer" class="author url fn" rel="author">Mike Lauer</a></span></div></span>
      </div>
      <div><p>We are pleased to announce that NIH recently released its Fiscal Years 2023-2027 NIH-Wide Strategic Plan for Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Accessibility (DEIA).</p>
</div>
      <div class="tags-field"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/diversity/" rel="tag">Diversity</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/diversity-equity-inclusion-and-accessibility/" rel="tag">diversity equity inclusion and accessibility</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/scientific-workforce-diversity/" rel="tag">scientific workforce diversity</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/strategic-plan/" rel="tag">strategic plan</a></div>
      <div class="comments-bubble">
        <p><span class="bubble number">1</span> <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2023/03/20/learn-about-nihs-diversity-equity-inclusion-and-accessibility-strategic-plan-for-fy-2023-to-2027/#comments">Comments</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- .entry-list-content -->

</article><!-- #post-24175 -->

<article id="post-24103" class="post-24103 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-open-mike tag-diversity tag-funding-data tag-scientific-workforce-diversity Issue-late-march-2023">
	<div class="entry-list-content">
		    
    <div class="list-block">
      <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2023/03/16/mentored-career-development-application-k-funding-rates-by-race-ethnicity-fy-2010-fy-2022/" rel="bookmark">Mentored Career Development Application (K) Funding Rates by Race-Ethnicity FY 2010-FY 2022</a></h2>      <div class="date-field">March 16, 2023</div>
      <div class="author-field">
        <span><div class="author-meta">By <span><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/lauerm/" title="Posts by Mike Lauer" class="author url fn" rel="author">Mike Lauer</a> and <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/marie-a-bernard/" title="Posts by Marie A. Bernard" class="author url fn" rel="author">Marie A. Bernard</a></span></div></span>
      </div>
      <div><p>In this post, we analyze funding rates for Fiscal Year (FY) 2010 to FY 2022 mentored career development award (K) applicants according to the race-ethnicity of designated Principal Investigators (PIs).</p>
</div>
      <div class="tags-field"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/diversity/" rel="tag">Diversity</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/funding-data/" rel="tag">Funding data</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/scientific-workforce-diversity/" rel="tag">scientific workforce diversity</a></div>
      <div class="comments-bubble">
        <p><span class="bubble number">6</span> <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2023/03/16/mentored-career-development-application-k-funding-rates-by-race-ethnicity-fy-2010-fy-2022/#comments">Comments</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- .entry-list-content -->

</article><!-- #post-24103 -->

<article id="post-24129" class="post-24129 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-open-mike tag-diversity tag-funding-data tag-scientific-workforce-diversity Issue-late-march-2023">
	<div class="entry-list-content">
		    
    <div class="list-block">
      <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2023/03/16/analyses-of-demographic-specific-funding-rates-for-type-1-research-project-grant-and-r01-equivalent-applications/" rel="bookmark">Analyses of Demographic-Specific Funding Rates for Type 1 Research Project Grant and R01-Equivalent Applications</a></h2>      <div class="date-field">March 16, 2023</div>
      <div class="author-field">
        <span><div class="author-meta">By <span><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/lauerm/" title="Posts by Mike Lauer" class="author url fn" rel="author">Mike Lauer</a> and <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/marie-bernard/" title="Posts by Marie A. Bernard" class="author url fn" rel="author">Marie A. Bernard</a></span></div></span>
      </div>
      <div><p>In this post, we analyze funding rates for Fiscal Year (FY) 2010 to FY 2022 Type 1 Research Project Grant (RPG) and Type 1 R01-Equivalent applicants according to the race-ethnicity of designated Principal Investigators (PIs).</p>
</div>
      <div class="tags-field"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/diversity/" rel="tag">Diversity</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/funding-data/" rel="tag">Funding data</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/scientific-workforce-diversity/" rel="tag">scientific workforce diversity</a></div>
      <div class="comments-bubble">
        <p><span class="bubble number">36</span> <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2023/03/16/analyses-of-demographic-specific-funding-rates-for-type-1-research-project-grant-and-r01-equivalent-applications/#comments">Comments</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- .entry-list-content -->

</article><!-- #post-24129 -->

<article id="post-23209" class="post-23209 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-open-mike tag-diversity tag-funding-data tag-funding-rate tag-grants Issue-june-2022">
	<div class="entry-list-content">
		    
    <div class="list-block">
      <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2022/06/14/research-project-grant-funding-rates-and-principal-investigator-race-and-ethnicity/" rel="bookmark">Research Project Grant Funding Rates and Principal Investigator Race and Ethnicity</a></h2>      <div class="date-field">June 14, 2022</div>
      <div class="author-field">
        <span><div class="author-meta">By <span><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/lauerm/" title="Posts by Mike Lauer" class="author url fn" rel="author">Mike Lauer</a> and <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/marie-bernard/" title="Posts by Marie A. Bernard" class="author url fn" rel="author">Marie A. Bernard</a></span></div></span>
      </div>
      <div><p>NIH has long collected self-designated demographic information on scientists designated as Principal Investigators (PIs) or Key Personnel and used this information to gain insights into the NIH-supported biomedical research workforce.</p>
</div>
      <div class="tags-field"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/diversity/" rel="tag">Diversity</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/funding-data/" rel="tag">Funding data</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/funding-rate/" rel="tag">funding rate</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/grants/" rel="tag">grants</a></div>
      <div class="comments-bubble">
        <p><span class="bubble number">42</span> <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2022/06/14/research-project-grant-funding-rates-and-principal-investigator-race-and-ethnicity/#comments">Comments</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- .entry-list-content -->

</article><!-- #post-23209 -->

<article id="post-22556" class="post-22556 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-open-mike tag-covid-19 tag-diversity Issue-early-march-2022">
	<div class="entry-list-content">
		    
    <div class="list-block">
      <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2022/02/24/how-virtual-convenings-can-enhance-diversity-equity-inclusion-and-accessibility/" rel="bookmark">How Virtual Convenings Can Enhance Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Accessibility</a></h2>      <div class="date-field">February 24, 2022</div>
      <div class="author-field">
        <span><div class="author-meta">By <span><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/marie-a-bernard/" title="Posts by Marie A. Bernard" class="author url fn" rel="author">Marie A. Bernard</a></span></div></span>
      </div>
      <div><p>Our latest guest post describes the NIH Chief Officer for Scientific Workforce Diversity Office&#8217;s commitment to hold all seminars, conferences, and meetings entirely online throughout 2022. The COVID-19 pandemic-induced shift to online events has led to a growing body of research on the impact of virtual scientific convenings. A review of this literature suggests that an entirely or primarily virtual format can enhance meeting access, diversity, and climate. </p>
</div>
      <div class="tags-field"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/covid-19/" rel="tag">COVID-19</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/diversity/" rel="tag">Diversity</a></div>
      <div class="comments-bubble">
        <p><span class="bubble number">0</span> <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2022/02/24/how-virtual-convenings-can-enhance-diversity-equity-inclusion-and-accessibility/#comments">Comments</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- .entry-list-content -->

</article><!-- #post-22556 -->

<article id="post-22504" class="post-22504 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-open-mike tag-administrative-supplements tag-diversity Issue-late-february-2022">
	<div class="entry-list-content">
		    
    <div class="list-block">
      <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2022/02/09/new-nih-administrative-supplements-available-to-support-diversity-mentorship/" rel="bookmark">New NIH Administrative Supplements Available to Support Diversity Mentorship</a></h2>      <div class="date-field">February 9, 2022</div>
      <div class="author-field">
        <span><div class="author-meta">By <span><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/author/marie-a-bernard/" title="Posts by Marie A. Bernard" class="author url fn" rel="author">Marie A. Bernard</a></span></div></span>
      </div>
      <div><p>I am pleased to announce the availability of a new NIH administrative supplement that recognizes the crucial role outstanding mentors play in fostering future leaders in the biomedical research enterprise. Qualified investigators can now submit proposals in response to the Chief Officer for Scientific Workforce Diversity (COSWD)-led Notice of Special Interest (NOSI) NOT-OD-22-057: Administrative Supplements to Recognize Excellence in Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Accessibility (DEIA) Mentorship. Proposals are due by April 7, 2022.</p>
</div>
      <div class="tags-field"><a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/administrative-supplements/" rel="tag">administrative supplements</a>, <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/tag/diversity/" rel="tag">Diversity</a></div>
      <div class="comments-bubble">
        <p><span class="bubble number">5</span> <a href="https://nexus.od.nih.gov/all/2022/02/09/new-nih-administrative-supplements-available-to-support-diversity-mentorship/#comments">Comments</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- .entry-list-content -->

</article><!-- #post-22504 -->

<article id="post-22402" class="post-22402 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-open-mike tag-deia tag-diversity tag-diversity-equity-inclusion-and-accessibility tag-request-for-information-rfi tag-rfi Issue-early-february-2022">
